      <section eId="sec_462">
        <num>462</num>
        <heading>Interlocal agreements authorized</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_462__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The exchange, furnishing or providing by one or more of the\ncontracting public agencies to one or more of the other contracting\npublic agencies of services, personnel, facilities, equipment, or any\nother property or resources for any one or more of the following\npurposes or uses:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Fire prevention and fire fighting\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Supply of water, gas or electricity\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Garbage collection and disposal\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Sewage disposal\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_5">
            <num>(5)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Refuse collection and disposal, and public dumps\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_6">
            <num>(6)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Storm drainage\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_7">
            <num>(7)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Airports or landing fields\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_8">
            <num>(8)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Parks, playgrounds, swimming pools, recreation centers,\n       or other recreational areas or facilities\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_9">
            <num>(9)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Youth counselling and guidance\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_10">
            <num>(10)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Municipal planning services\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_11">
            <num>(11)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Engineering services\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_12">
            <num>(12)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Lighting\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_13">
            <num>(13)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Ambulance service\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_14">
            <num>(14)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Fire and police radio and communication systems\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_15">
            <num>(15)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Hospital service\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_16">
            <num>(16)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Public health services\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_17">
            <num>(17)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Mental health services\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_18">
            <num>(18)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Cemeteries\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_19">
            <num>(19)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Libraries or bookmobiles\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_20">
            <num>(20)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Suppression or control of plant and\n       animal pests or diseases\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_21">
            <num>(21)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Propagation of game, game birds or fish\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_22">
            <num>(22)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Publicizing the advantages of the region\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_462__subsec_a__subsec_23">
            <num>(23)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Roads and highways.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_462__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The establishment of an interlocal advisory board or boards to\nrecommend programs and policies for cooperative or uniform action in any\nfields of activity enumerated in paragraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_462__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of this subdivision and\npermitted or authorized for each contracting public agency, and from\ntime to time to advise with the appropriate officials of the contracting\npublic agencies in respect to such programs, policies or fields of\nactivity.\n  2. Nothing contained in this article shall be construed to authorize\nor permit any public agency of this state to receive, obtain, furnish or\nprovide services, facilities, personnel, equipment, or any other\nproperty or resources, or to engage in or perform any function or\nactivity by means of an interlocal agreement if it does not have\nconstitutional or statutory power or authorization to receive, obtain,\nfurnish or provide the same or substantially similar services,\nfacilities, personnel, equipment, other property or resources, or to\nengage in or perform the same or a substantially similar function or\nactivity on its own account.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
